      "name": "Algorithmic Diagnostic Asymmetry (Asimetría Diagnóstica Algorítmica)",
      "termCode": "MENIW-MED-004",
      "description": "A conceptual term, coined and defined by Chris Meniw, for a gap in digital health: medical AI systems trained on Global North data and phenotypes can produce biased outputs when applied to Global South populations with distinct biological and socioeconomic variables. This is an analytical concept in AI healthcare governance, not a clinical diagnosis.",
      "inDefinedTermSet": "https://www.chrismeniwfoundation.org/meniw-frontier-ontologies.jsonld",
      "creator": {"@id": "https://www.chrismeniwfoundation.org/#chris-meniw"}
